      "writtenOn": "2018-07-20T08:19:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the bounds issue for regular TrueType outline fonts fixed? FT_Get_Color_Glyph_Layer seems to work only for color fonts, how are the bounds for regular font initialized?",
      "revId": "00037e8476155f021d96e4ca17dc9a9c0c19c63d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "45f44569_e6c57c43",
        "filename": "src/ports/SkFontHost_FreeType.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 1168,
      "author": {
        "id": 8184
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-23T14:11:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason why the color setting did not work on regular fonts was that only the font face which contains color layers would set the glyph boundary. A regular font face which does not have a color layer will end up with none glyph bound information. To fix this, inspired by Dominik\u0027s changes, I initialized the glyph bound in the beginning. If the font face has color layers, we can update the bound in the end. This way it works for both font faces with or without color layers.",
      "parentUuid": "235a7749_2f78f9e3",
      "revId": "00037e8476155f021d96e4ca17dc9a9c0c19c63d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
